            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="xpu-Latn" resp="#JP" source="http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/YHFC9RB5">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>bn <persName type="attested"><name>ʾd<unclear>r</unclear><supplied reason="lost">bʿl</supplied></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text after Coacci Polselli 1986.</note></app>
                    <app loc="1"><note>alternatively: ʾdn[---]</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#RDS">
                <p>[---] son of  ʾdr/n[---]</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#RDS">
                <p>[---] figlio di  ʾdr/n[---]</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#RDS">
                <p>The text contains part of a votive inscription of which only the genealogy remains with the initial part of a Phoenician anthroponym to be completed as <foreign xml:lang="xpu-Latn">ʾdr[bʿl]</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="xpu-Latn">ʾdn[bʿl]</foreign>.</p>
            </div>
